Quixote Corp said Dainippon Ink andChemicals Inc of Japan will buy 526,315 shares of Quixotecommon stock, a 6.7 pct stake, for 10 mln dlrs, or 19 dlrs ashare.    It said the two companies also agreed to share the resultsof their research and development activities in optical disctechnology.    Dainippon Inc's optical disc technology focuses on thedevelopment of a new Direct-Read-After-Write optical disc andan advanced erasable optical disc.    Quixote said its wholly owned subsidiary, LaserVideo Inc,is making advancements in the art of mastering andmanufacturing Compact Discs, CD-ROMs and laser-read videodiscs.    Quixote said the agreement with Dainippon, which has annualsales of more than two billion dlrs, provides for a Dainipponrepresentative to sit on the LaserVideo board of directors. Reuter&#3;